Base.Explanation: Setup a session with the Powershell Agent service. The session is requied for a number of UMRA script actions that use the Powershell Agent service. See the online help for more information.

ArrayElement.Name: Session ID
ArrayElement.Description: The identifier of the Powershell Agent service session. The value should be stored in a variable that is used in subsequent UMRA acions thath use the Powershell Agent service session. This property is an 'output only' property. By default, the value for this property is stored in variable %PowershellAgentSessionId%.

Base.Explanation: Load Powershell Connector into the current Powershell session.

Base.Name: Session ID
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the Powershell Agent service session.

Base.Name: Connector DLL file
Base.Description: Full path of the connector DLL file

Base.Explanation: Add a new application enrollment in E-SSOM.

Base.Name: Session ID
Base.Description: This parameter identifies the Powershell Agent service session.

Base.Name: E-SSOM server
Base.Description: The address of the E-SSOM server.

Base.Name: E-SSOM server port
Base.Description: The communication port for the E-SSOM server connection.

Base.Name: Username
Base.Description: Username of the account to be enrolled.

Base.Name: Domain
Base.Description: Domain of the account to be enrolled.

Base.Name: Application variables
Base.Description: The variables for this application. This uses an ENCRYPTED variable as input. Format: [variableName|fieldType|variableValue] Variable divider: "#" Example: userName|string|F. vanhaaster#password|string|myPassword Valid fieldTypes are: [string, number, bool, fileTime] (Do not add the '%' characters to the variableName, this will be done automatically, otherwise UMRA will replace these values with variable content.) For the "bool" fieldType use an UMRA boolean variable or [1 / 0] or [true / false]

Base.Name: retVal
Base.Description: This will be 0 when the action executes successfully. If an error occured during execution, the value will be 1.

Base.Explanation: Release a session with the Powershell Agent service. The session should be previously setup with action 'Setup Powershell Agent service session'. The session is identified by property 'Session ID'.

ArrayElement.Name: Session ID
ArrayElement.Description: The identifier of the Powershell Agent service session. The value should correspond with property 'Session ID' of action 'Setup Powershell Agent service session', called previously.
